  <title>Missing information for whole-screen colour correction?</title>
  <p>Unfortunately, many vendor-supplied ICC profiles do not include the information required for whole-screen colour correction. These profiles can still be useful for applications that can do colour compensation, but you will not see all the colours of your screen change.</p>
  <p>In order to create a display profile, which includes both calibration and characterisation data, you will need to use a special colour measuring instruments called a colorimeter or a spectrometer.</p>

